Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.81,0:00:03.99,Default,OLD MAN,0000,0000,0000,,The path of the warrior is without end.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.48,0:00:08.37,Default,OLD MAN,0000,0000,0000,,You've taken yet another step \Ntoward mastering its secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.08,0:00:12.69,Default,OLD MAN,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing left for me to teach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.11,0:00:15.62,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You say that every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.45,0:00:20.11,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Fern?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.11,0:00:21.46,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.46,0:00:23.89,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,She's pissed? Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.72,0:00:25.99,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.09,0:00:39.01,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,You're there like the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.01,0:00:43.64,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Closing your eyes at sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.64,0:00:49.27,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's on your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.57,0:00:54.61,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(857,1)\blur0.25\fs35\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\c&HFFFE65&\pos(328,254)\clip(109,253,547,294)\t(3943,4986,\clip(109,253,110,294))}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.99,0:00:57.99,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With your eyelids open
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.99,0:01:02.58,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes shone like glass
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.58,0:01:09.34,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It faintly smelled like a sunny day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.26,0:01:20.47,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Clear up the sky, let flowers bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.47,0:01:24.68,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Bloom and blame it on the sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.68,0:01:29.06,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the rain, when it stops
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.06,0:01:34.07,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Will make you shine in the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.07,0:01:39.45,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Calm the stirring sounds in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.45,0:01:43.49,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We go like the sunny wind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.49,0:01:47.92,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and fly over that cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:52.75,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Further and further away
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.01,0:01:59.01,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(392,269.5)}Episode 27: An Era of Humans
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.97,0:02:02.39,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren and I had an argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.66,0:02:06.01,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Again? You've been arguing a lot recently, \Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:10.03,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't the third test the final one?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.03,0:02:12.02,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This is hardly the time to be squabbling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:14.15,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She was truly awful this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:18.39,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,My staff broke in battle \Nin the Ruins of the King's Tomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.02,0:02:22.66,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,so I told Ms. Frieren \NI wanted to get it repaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.08,0:02:28.22,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She told me it'd be better to buy \Na new staff than to repair my old one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.22,0:02:29.80,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You mean that staff, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.14,0:02:33.14,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,She said it couldn't be repaired \Nsince it was already in pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.19,0:02:40.40,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Still, Mr. Heiter gave me that staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.68,0:02:45.57,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's been with me ever since I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.76,0:02:50.03,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We're talking about Frieren, though. \NI doubt she meant any harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.76,0:02:56.01,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, I never even \Nwould have thought of throwing it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.09,0:03:02.41,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Three years until the next \Nfirst-class mage exam, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.85,0:03:05.27,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Three years is a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.27,0:03:07.53,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Just make fun of me like you always do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.54,0:03:11.37,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want me to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.01,0:03:12.90,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.14,0:03:18.43,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Little Miss Lawine, \Nshall I pat your head?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.42,0:03:24.57,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,What? You wanna fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.83,0:03:29.18,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.10,0:03:32.13,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,You're in really rough shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.59,0:03:36.57,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:47.03,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.43,0:03:51.91,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how long are you going \Nto hang around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.37,0:03:55.92,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I failed the test. There's nothing \Nkeeping us together anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.29,0:03:58.56,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,You're interfering with my business. \NGet out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.81,0:04:02.90,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here as a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.79,0:04:05.81,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Then hurry up and choose something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.63,0:04:11.57,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,You can have some.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.57,0:04:12.38,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want any.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.35,0:04:15.82,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You were unlucky this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.17,0:04:20.27,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You got the short end of the stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.27,0:04:24.33,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It could've happened to \Nanyone in that position.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.61,0:04:28.57,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,A loss is a loss. I wasn't strong enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.24,0:04:31.59,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, don't bring that up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.12,0:04:35.08,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I may seem fine, but I'm actually \Nin a terrible mood right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.77,0:04:38.33,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,But you opened your shop regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.73,0:04:44.18,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Denken, you may not realize this,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.18,0:04:48.98,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,but people have to work to make a living \Nno matter how foul their mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.68,0:04:53.97,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.79,0:04:59.99,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's for the best \Nthat I'm the one who failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.99,0:05:02.98,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,The first-class mage exam \Nis held once every three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.98,0:05:08.61,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,A decrepit old man like you might not \Nbe around three years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.42,0:05:11.12,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.12,0:05:12.57,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Don't agree with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.44,0:05:21.84,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Richter, you truly are an insolent youngster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.23,0:05:24.01,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You mock authority
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.01,0:05:28.33,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,and have no qualms about mistreating \Nthe weak in order to achieve your goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.70,0:05:31.97,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Your behavior is hardly praiseworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:36.79,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,And yet I feel no hatred for you at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.68,0:05:42.60,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,probably because I was once \Nan insolent youngster too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.32,0:05:49.25,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,And now, I'm an imperial mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:51.36,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:55.48,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you not to be so discouraged.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.88,0:06:00.02,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Three years from now, you'll be \Nfar stronger than you are today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.13,0:06:02.79,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Laufen, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.24,0:06:09.23,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. The old man's not good with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.23,0:06:11.47,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,What's your relationship with Denken, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.70,0:06:16.14,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.34,0:06:19.76,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't buy anything after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.05,0:06:35.91,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Is today my unlucky day or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.91,0:06:43.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I asked around town and was told this shop \Ncan fix any staff, no matter how broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.84,0:06:46.13,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Show me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:52.86,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,What is this broken pile of scrapwood? \NDon't tell me this is meant to be a staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:55.68,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a trash disposal service, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.68,0:06:57.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.89,0:06:58.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.24,0:07:09.31,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,My mood was starting to improve, \Nbut because of you, I feel terrible again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.78,0:07:13.54,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I have the right to choose \Nwhich jobs I work on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.94,0:07:15.41,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,You should give up on this staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.97,0:07:17.81,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.34,0:07:21.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't do it, then never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.23,0:07:27.33,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, you really get on my nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.56,0:07:31.09,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,When did I say I couldn't do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.86,0:07:40.49,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Can you finish today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.78,0:07:43.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I want it to be repaired \Nin time for the third test.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.40,0:07:45.28,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.38,0:07:51.58,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.58,0:07:52.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.98,0:07:55.05,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for calling it trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.42,0:07:58.81,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good, well-maintained staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.20,0:08:01.88,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Someone must've taken really good care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.08,0:08:09.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Fern, let's head back already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.60,0:08:15.89,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren doesn't understand me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.89,0:08:18.46,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand you either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.77,0:08:21.97,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Don't take it out on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.03,0:08:28.24,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What matters is that she \N{\i1}tries{\i0} to understand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.53,0:08:30.93,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I think Frieren is doing her best.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.25,0:08:42.51,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,You're Frieren's kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.03,0:08:44.39,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Her student, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.74,0:08:47.80,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:50.38,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.19,0:08:56.39,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, the second test \Nonly ended yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:08:59.88,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,but I had another terrible day \Nbecause of your master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.31,0:09:06.28,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I would've made more profit \Nif you'd just bought a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.57,0:09:08.88,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Take good care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.94,0:09:26.53,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,My staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.64,0:09:37.54,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren struggles to understand emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.54,0:09:42.49,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it will cause \Ndifficulties and disagreements.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.28,0:09:46.74,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,But there is one good thing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.07,0:09:52.73,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren will worry and care \Nabout you just as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.47,0:09:57.47,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Few masters are better than her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.84,0:10:35.11,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, about yesterday…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.12,0:10:37.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.44,0:10:42.68,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.92,0:10:44.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:51.13,Default,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,The third test will now begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:11:00.62,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why I came \Nall the way here, Sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.36,0:11:05.01,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing to say, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:07.88,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You always remain silent\Nin troublesome situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.96,0:11:12.10,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Twelve test-takers passed the second test.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.10,0:11:15.56,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's an anomaly. It's too many.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.12,0:11:19.69,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I have no problem with a test that requires \Nall participants to work together,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.01,0:11:24.07,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,as the current first-class mages \Nlack cooperativeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.07,0:11:25.65,Flashback,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.66,0:11:32.20,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,But there is one among the test-takers \Nwho is far too powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.51,0:11:35.57,Flashback,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.64,0:11:40.81,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Because of her, many have passed \Ndespite lacking the requisite strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.26,0:11:46.51,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,A typical third test would kill all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.25,0:11:51.72,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Sense, that's hardly what you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.32,0:11:57.31,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,and not even I wish to see \Nsuch pointless deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.81,0:11:59.10,Flashback,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Serie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.36,0:12:03.45,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to apologize. \NIt's all Frieren's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.69,0:12:06.58,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,An anomaly calls for an anomaly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.13,0:12:09.80,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I will proctor the third test.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.20,0:12:13.57,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It will be a peaceful selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.48,0:12:17.65,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,In past years, you've proctored the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.77,0:12:20.87,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You don't object, do you, Lernen?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:28.38,Flashback,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Your willfulness is nothing new, Ms. Serie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.66,0:12:33.81,Flashback,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I could not \Npossibly test Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.45,0:12:39.91,Flashback,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,I could tell at a glance that \Nshe's suppressing her own mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.25,0:12:46.67,Flashback,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Her mana is tremendous, equal to yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.08,0:12:52.55,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Falsch, did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.55,0:12:55.36,Flashback,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,No, I have no idea \Nwhat he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.80,0:12:59.34,Flashback,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,I observed her mana myself \Nat the testing area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.80,0:13:03.35,Flashback,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't seem to me like \Nshe was suppressing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.80,0:13:07.69,Flashback,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,I observed none of the typical fluctuations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.23,0:13:13.44,Flashback,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,No living creature with mana \Ncan conceal these fluctuations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:18.70,Flashback,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it were possible, it would take \Nan extraordinary amount of time to master.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.19,0:13:22.08,Flashback,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,It would hardly be a practical skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.32,0:13:27.69,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren has devoted her life \Nto mastering that impractical skill
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.59,0:13:30.69,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,in order to deceive demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.84,0:13:39.04,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Demons are far more sensitive \Nto mana than us humanoids.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.04,0:13:45.85,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Without innate talent, it takes more than \Na century or two of practice to fool them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:48.46,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It truly is a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.19,0:13:54.13,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You'd become far more powerful devoting \Nyour efforts to training something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.13,0:13:55.97,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's incredibly inefficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.83,0:14:01.60,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,But that inefficiency \Nbreeds weakness in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.01,0:14:05.03,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,In a battle between experienced mages,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.03,0:14:09.37,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,miscalculating your opponent's mana \Ncan lead directly to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.78,0:14:15.34,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren is in fact relatively \Nunskilled for her age,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.34,0:14:17.95,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,and yet she's defeated demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.97,0:14:24.11,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Her mana control is simply that refined.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.11,0:14:29.06,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,As far as I knew, only the Demon King \Nwas able to see through it at first glance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.25,0:14:33.84,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,That is, until this moment, Lernen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.24,0:14:40.41,Flashback,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a coincidence. I just happened \Nto see a minor fluctuation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.41,0:14:42.11,Flashback,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:45.74,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Ever modest and dependable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.16,0:14:52.58,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's been more than half a century since \Nyou became the first first-class mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.72,0:14:58.05,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,But you're still the same timid boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.09,0:15:02.10,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,That's my only disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.37,0:15:08.41,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You've achieved this level, and yet \Nyou don't have much longer to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.53,0:15:14.67,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt you'll ever get the \Nchance to fight Frieren,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.49,0:15:18.34,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,even if it's a battle you could win.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.79,0:15:24.10,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't take on human students.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.69,0:15:27.58,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's truly disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.15,0:15:36.77,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, that boy never saw \Nthe fluctuations in my mana either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.94,0:15:44.30,Default,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,The third test will be an interview \Nwith Serie the Great Mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.89,0:15:46.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it's going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.89,0:15:48.02,DefaultTop,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,You will be called one at a time \Nwhen she is ready for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.61,0:15:50.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Serie intends to fail us both.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.02,0:15:50.10,DefaultTop,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait here until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.02,0:15:52.00,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You know her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.00,0:15:53.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,From a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.14,0:15:57.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She probably intends to choose who passes \Nbased on her intuition.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:16:01.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But Serie's intuition is always right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.08,0:16:06.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I still haven't become the mage \NSerie wishes I were.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:41.51,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.51,0:16:43.90,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You fail. Now leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.37,0:16:47.65,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.10,0:16:55.16,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,My mana frightens you. \NYou know the limits of your own abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.69,0:16:59.90,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You can't imagine yourself \Nas a first-class mage, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.36,0:17:04.90,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,In the world of magic, that which \Ncan't be visualized cannot be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.48,0:17:07.78,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's the most fundamental principle. \NNow leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.75,0:17:09.74,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.03,0:17:11.04,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.25,0:17:12.32,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.52,0:17:13.76,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.94,0:17:22.19,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, you can't imagine yourself \Nas a first-class mage either,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.72,0:17:25.69,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,but for a different reason \Nfrom the rest of the test-takers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.20,0:17:31.06,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You don't believe I'd ever let you pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.06,0:17:32.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:38.10,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you one chance. \NTell me your favorite spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.45,0:17:40.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A spell to create a field of flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.03,0:17:45.57,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,That's the spell Flamme taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.03,0:17:47.84,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,How truly useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.84,0:17:49.26,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.08,0:17:51.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.78,0:17:59.98,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You won't even stand your ground \Nwhen I mock you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.98,0:18:04.99,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I find it hard to believe a mage \Nlike you defeated the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.61,0:18:09.97,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.41,0:18:14.83,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel, Eisen, Heiter, and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.83,0:18:17.53,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If any one of us hadn't been there, \Nwe couldn't have won.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.12,0:18:20.35,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,So you were blessed with strong allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.75,0:18:22.26,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You were lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.05,0:18:26.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I was lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.40,0:18:32.55,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel, why did you recruit me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.00,0:18:37.01,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Because I was looking for a powerful mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.01,0:18:39.82,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There are plenty of powerful mages \Nin the royal capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.30,0:18:42.02,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't have to be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.43,0:18:44.51,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.99,0:18:46.02,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.23,0:18:54.84,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, you may not remember, \Nbut I once met you a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.42,0:18:57.45,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I don't remember that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.45,0:18:58.81,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I know you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.64,0:19:04.65,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a child, I got lost \Nwhile gathering herbs in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.30,0:19:08.93,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Wandering the woods for hours at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.93,0:19:11.87,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I experienced loneliness \Nfor the first time in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.78,0:19:16.17,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd never be able \Nto return to my village.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.27,0:19:23.76,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,That was when a lone elf pointed me \Nin the direction of the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.93,0:19:30.05,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,All she did was show me which way it was. \NShe spoke not a word of encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.70,0:19:34.73,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,To the eyes of a child, \Nshe seemed so cold-hearted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:41.03,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps she sensed my unease, \Nor perhaps it was on a whim...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.14,0:19:51.22,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You showed me a spell \Nto create a field of flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.00,0:19:58.81,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.98,0:20:03.98,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,For the first time in my life, \NI thought magic was beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.25,0:20:11.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably just a coincidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.51,0:20:14.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but it was that useless spell \Nmy master taught me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.52,0:20:17.62,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,that brought me and my companions together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:25.87,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Also, Serie, I'm sure you intend \Nto fail Fern as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.35,0:20:28.24,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but I doubt you'll be able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.00,0:20:33.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She will exceed your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.11,0:20:36.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The era of humans has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.13,0:20:42.25,DefaultItalics,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Exceed my expectations? Hardly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.97,0:20:45.64,DefaultItalics,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,The sight of my mana has her frozen in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.21,0:20:48.65,DefaultItalics,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,She's no different from the other test-takers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.68,0:20:58.71,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. What do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.70,0:21:05.27,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's fluctuating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.14,0:21:10.82,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Fern, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.78,0:21:14.40,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Be my student.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.02,0:21:17.15,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.56,0:21:24.51,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I'll treat you well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.52,0:21:29.52,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I can take you to greater heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.18,0:21:36.45,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,To heights no other mage has ever reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.30,0:21:42.23,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Does this affect whether or not I pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.96,0:21:44.60,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.94,0:21:49.31,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.31,0:21:52.63,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Serie.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.69,0:22:02.59,FlashbackItalics,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.30,0:22:06.32,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Serie will have \Na lot of things to say to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.32,0:22:08.54,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no need for you \Nto accept her demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.40,0:22:13.26,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Just as Serie will fail me \Nno matter what I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.26,0:22:16.24,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,she will pass you no matter what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.60,0:22:21.02,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,After all, Serie's intuition is always right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.13,0:22:26.56,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I am Ms. Frieren's student.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.67,0:22:35.56,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren coached you, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.48,0:22:40.27,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not foolish enough \Nto overlook a promising mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.66,0:22:43.95,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.24,0:22:49.18,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.97,0:22:53.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm alright (I'll be alright)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.10,0:22:56.02,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I hear you (I care about you)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.02,0:23:01.61,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The wind teases this hair that's longer now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.61,0:23:04.02,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's meaning in everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.53,0:23:07.03,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the days that came to a halt
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.61,0:23:13.66,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I finally understand,\NI've caught up to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.66,0:23:17.45,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.45,0:23:20.33,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.33,0:23:25.00,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.00,0:23:31.26,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ask to see you, so at least
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.26,0:23:37.02,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Let me remember the past, just for today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.02,0:23:43.02,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.02,0:23:48.90,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,No more hesitations, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.99,0:23:52.95,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere, yah (wherever you are)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.95,0:23:57.58,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere (smile for me)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.58,0:24:00.58,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be there (close your eyes,\Nand I'll always be there)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.58,0:24:03.33,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if there are no absolutes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.33,0:24:06.38,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always aware of your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.38,0:24:12.43,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright,\Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.89,0:24:19.35,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm whispering our lullaby\Nfor you to come back home
